EquuSearch was in the process of suing Anthony when she filed for bankruptcy earlier this year.

Judge K. Rodney May partially granted Anthony’s motion to dismiss, giving Texas EquuSearch 21 days to amend its complaint against Anthony, reported NBC News.

In June her lawyers said she could be at risk of 'disappearing' if the defamation cases against her continue.

